        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 29 at 4:44PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 444 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fowler, or 27 miles west of La Junta, moving north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fowler.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
